Add snapshot testing

* Add snapshot testing

* Add TravisCI

Fixing tests by stubing system date

According to jest snapshot testing documentation
(https://facebook.github.io/jest/docs/snapshot-testing.html) tests
should be deterministic that means that every time they run should
return the same result, but that was not possible with the previous
approach because the date was changing every time tests runs, by stubbing
the date, tests can be deterministic again.

chore: update Prettier to v3 (#2577)

Believe or not, this is a necessary step to e.g. update Rollup, which, following Node.js, started requiring import assertions on JSON imports, which Prettier v1 does not support.

Note: all changes are automatic unless otherwise specified.

- Updated ESLint from 6.8.0 to 8.56.0
- Updated all ESLint plugins
- Swapped babel-eslint for @typescript-eslint/parser (adds ability to e.g. use import assertions, necessary to lint Rollup config files, and potentially more in the future)
- Revised the list of rules (many were turned on by plugin updates) to avoid breakages; list to be revised later, we may decide to gracefully turn on the new rules and fix the issues.
